'''Andreas Rædergård Schjelderup''' (born 1 June 2004) is a Norwegian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder#Winger|left winger]] or [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Primeira Liga]] club [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]].

==Club career==
===Early years===
Born in [[Bodø (town)|Bodø]], Norway,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Toresen |first1=Freddy |last2=Høgland |first2=Stian |title=Stortalentet glipper for Glimt: – Hadde egentlig lagt Glimt bak meg i fjor |url=https://www.an.no/stortalentet-glipper-for-glimt-hadde-egentlig-lagt-glimt-bak-meg-i-fjor/s/5-4-1229694 |work=Avisa Nordland |date=7 July 2020 |language=no}}</ref> Schjelderup began his career in the youth sector at [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]].<ref name=TVtwo>{{cite web|url=https://www.tv2.no/a/11940368/|title="Hele" Europa ville ha Andreas (16): – Dette var beviset på at jeg valgte riktig|website=TV2|date=5 February 2021|accessdate=21 March 2021|language=Norwegian}}</ref> Schjelderup was coveted by many big clubs throughout Europe, including reported interest from clubs in top leagues in Italy, Spain and the Netherlands.

===Nordsjælland===
In July 2020, Schjelderup chose to move to Denmark to sign with [[Danish Superliga|Superliga]] club [[FC Nordsjælland|Nordsjælland]].<ref name=TVtwo/> He was promoted to the Nordsjælland first team following the winter break during the [[2020–21 FC Nordsjælland season|2020–21 season]]. He made his senior debut from the starting eleven, in a 2–0 defeat to [[Odense Boldklub|OB]] on 7 February 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.superliga.dk/kamp/2020-2021/februar/fc-nordsjaelland-ob|title=FCN 0:2 OB|website=Superliga|date=7 February 2021|accessdate=21 March 2021|language=Danish}}</ref> Aged 16 years and 248 days old, he became the 13th youngest player in Superliga history.<ref name=TVtwo/> He scored his first senior goal for the club in a 3–0 win over local rivals [[Lyngby Boldklub|Lyngby]] on 12 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://spielverlagerung.com/2021/03/13/fcn-win-derby-battle/|title=FCN win derby battle|website=Spielverlagerung|date=13 March 2021|accessdate=21 March 2021}}</ref> In doing so, he became the club's record youngest goalscorer in Superliga history, edging out teammate [[Tochi Chukwuani]]'s record set the previous season, and the fourth youngest overall in league history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fcn.dk/2021/03/andreas-schjelderup-er-yngste-fcn-maalscorer-i-superligaen-nogensinde/|title=ANDREAS SCHJELDERUP ER YNGSTE FCN-MÅLSCORER I SUPERLIGAEN NOGENSINDE|website=FCN|date=12 March 2021|accessdate=21 March 2021|language=Danish|archive-date=27 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211127192358/https://fcn.dk/2021/03/andreas-schjelderup-er-yngste-fcn-maalscorer-i-superligaen-nogensinde/|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 21 March, the final day of the [[2020–21 Danish Superliga]] regular season, Schjelderup scored both goals in Nordsjælland's 2–1 defeat of [[SønderjyskE Fodbold|SønderjyskE]], leapfrogging his club above SønderjyskE and into sixth place, securing the final spot in the Superliga championship play-offs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nettavisen.no/sport/to-klassemal-da-andreas-schjelderup-herjet-for-nordsjalland/s/12-95-3424104989|title=Takket være den norske 16-åringen ble plassen i sluttspillet, og sjansen til å spille i europacuper sikret. I siste runde.|website=Nettavisen|date=21 March 2021|accessdate=21 March 2021|language=Danish}}</ref>

===Benfica===
On 12 January 2023, Schjelderup signed a five-year contract with [[Primeira Liga]] side [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2023/01/12/futebol-benfica-apresentacao-andreas-schjelderup-reforco-contratacao |title=Andreas Schjelderup é do Benfica! |work=S.L. Benfica |language=pt |date=12 January 2023 }}</ref> The fee reported by Portuguese media was around €14 million. Norwegian media reported, however, that the fee was 105 million kroner (approximately €10 million), and Nordsjælland also secured 20% of a potential future sale.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bold.dk/fodbold/stillinger/superligaen/nyheder/officielt-fcn-saelger-andreas-schjelderup-til-benfica/ |title=Officielt: FCN sælger Andreas Schjelderup til Benfica |work=bold.dk |language=da |date=12 January 2023 }}</ref> Schjelderup made his Benfica debut in the Primeira Liga, against Madeiran side [[CS Maritimo|Maritimo]] on 12 March 2023. Later on, Schjelderup made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut against Italian side [[Inter Milan]].

The Norwegian had a difficult start to his stay at Benfica. In the first six months, he only made two brief appearances for the first team, while he also made five appearances for the club's B team.

==== 2023–24 season: Return to Nordsjælland (loan) ====
On 2 September 2023, [[FC Nordsjælland|Nordsjælland]] announced that Schjelderup would be returning to the club on a season-long [[Loan (sports)|loan]] deal from Benfica,<ref>[https://fcn.dk/nyheder/2023/september/schjelderup-er-tilbage Han er tilbage: FCN lejer Andreas Schjelderup i SL Benfica], fcn.dk, 1 September 2023</ref> with the Danish club paying a €2.5 million loan fee.<ref>{{Cite web |date=5 September 2023 |title=Venda de Vlachodimos rendeu cerca de cinco milhões de euros ao Benfica |trans-title=Sale of Vlachodimos made Benfica around five million euros |url=https://www.jn.pt/3571545377/venda-de-vlachodimos-rendeu-cerca-de-cinco-milhoes-de-euros-ao-benfica/ |access-date=6 September 2023 |website= |publisher=[[Jornal de Notícias]] |language=pt-PT}}</ref> In May he was named the spring season's best player by Danish league managers.<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 May 2024 |title=Andreas Schjelderup eleito o melhor jogador da Liga dinamarquesa |trans-title=Andreas Schjelderup elected best player in the Danish league |url=https://poste.pt/benfica/33362/andreas-schjelderup-eleito-o-melhor-jogador-da-liga-dinamarquesa |access-date=24 May 2024 |website= |publisher=Poste |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

==== 2024–25 season: First-team breakthrough ====
On 27 October 2024, Schjelderup scored his first goal for Benfica in a 5–0 win over [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]] in the [[2024–25 Primeira Liga|Primeira Liga]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/en/liga/jogo/20242025/ligaportugalbetclic/9/1|title=SL Benfica 5:0 Rio Ave FC|website=Liga Portugal|date=27 October 2024|accessdate=11 January 2025|language=Portuguese}}</ref> On 11 January 2025, he scored in the [[2025 Taça da Liga final|final]] of the [[2024–25 Taça da Liga|Taça da Liga]] as Benfica defeated [[Sporting CP|Sporting]] on penalties following a 1–1 draw in normal time.<ref name=TdLwin>{{cite web|url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/liga/jogo/20242025/allianzcup/3/1|title=Sporting CP 1:1 SL Benfica|website=Liga Portugal|date=11 January 2025|language=Portuguese|access-date=11 January 2025|archive-date=14 January 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250114180512/https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/liga/jogo/20242025/allianzcup/3/1|url-status=dead}}</ref> Three days later, on 14 October 2024, he scored in the fifth round of the [[2024–25 Taça de Portugal|Taça de Portugal]] as Benfica won 1–3 away at [[S.C. Farense|Farense]].<ref name=TdPwin>{{cite web|url=https://resultados.fpf.pt/Match/GetMatchInformation?matchId=2255944|title=Farense  1:1 SL Benfica|website=Federação Portuguesa de Futebol |date=15 January 2025|language=Portuguese}}</ref>

On 24 June 2025, he scored the only goal in a 1–0 victory over [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], securing his club's first-ever win against the latter and top spot in Group C in the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/jun/24/club-world-cup-benfica-bayern-munich-chelsea-flamengo-lafc-boca-juniors |title=Club World Cup: Auckland City hold on for shock draw with Boca Juniors while Benfica top Bayern |publisher=The Guardian |date=25 June 2025 }}</ref>

==== 2025–26 season ====
On 12 August 2025, he was in the starting XI for Benfica against [[OGC Nice|Nice]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] third qualifying round. He assisted for the team's first goal and scored the second, helping secure a 2–0 win, 4–0 on aggregate, ensuring Benfica's sport in the play-off round.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2045721--benfica-vs-nice/ |title=Benfica-Nice match report|publisher=UEFA |date=12 August 2025 }}</ref> Later in the season, he completed an awards hat-trick after being named the Primeira Liga's Player of the Month, Forward of the Month and Young Player of the Month for April.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/schjelderup-completes-awards-hat-trick-with-april-player-prize-for-benfica-42870872 |title=Schjelderup completes awards hat-trick with April player prize for Benfica |publisher=OneFootball |date=15 May 2026 }}</ref> He finished the campaign with a career-best return of 10 goals and six assists for the club across all competitions.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/rui-costa-to-seek-more-than-30m-from-milan-for-benfica-regular-42876670 |title=Rui Costa 'to seek' more than €30m from Milan for Benfica regular |publisher=OneFootball |date=16 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Schjelderup has been capped at youth level for Norway. He made his debut for the senior team on 5 June 2024 in a friendly against Kosovo, coming on as a substitute for [[Erling Braut Haaland|Erling Haaland]].<ref>{{NFF|2723263}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Schjelderup is regarded as a highly skillful and technical player capable of playing in several offensive positions, due to his versatility; throughout his career, he has been deployed occasionally as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] or second striker, but even though his natural position is that of an [[attacking midfielder]], he plays primarily as a left winger. Schjelderup tends to hug the touchline off the ball. He receives possession from teammates out wide before cutting inside and driving towards more central areas, thus ensuring that he can pick up the ball with space and time before looking to make a real impact. Schjelderup also has the ability to draw defenders toward him. That opens up space for his teammates to exploit. Another aspect of his game is his dribbling, Schjelderup has extremely quick feet and excellent agility in one-on-one duels. When making attacking runs off the ball, Schjelderup’s main objective is to create lateral separation. He very rarely tries to make runs in behind, and instead prefers to make runs out wide and receive in front of the defence.<ref>{{Cite web|date=16 January 2023|title=ANDREAS SCHJELDERUP|url=https://www.scoutedftbl.com/best-young-football-players/andreas-schjelderup/|access-date=23 January 2023|website=www.scoutedftbl.com|language=en|archive-date=23 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230123231810/https://www.scoutedftbl.com/best-young-football-players/andreas-schjelderup/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Schjelderup idolises Norwegians [[Martin Ødegaard]] and [[Erling Haaland]], being compared to the latter due to his goalscoring abilities.<ref name=TVtwo/><ref>{{Cite web|date=4 October 2022|title=Andreas Schjelderup scout report: Another Norwegian goal-machine joins Benfica|url=https://www.foottheball.com/players-in-focus/andreas-schjelderup-stats-profile-norway-nordsjaelland-scout-report-transfer-news-skills-potential/|access-date=23 January 2023|website=www.foottheball.com|language=en}}</ref>

==Personal life==
On 19 November 2025, Schjelderup was convicted of a [[child pornography]] offence after he admitted to forwarding a [[Snapchat]] video containing two boys under the age of 18 engaging in sexual activity to four of his friends. He was handed a 14-day suspended sentence. He had previously posted a statement about the incident, which happened when he was 19, calling it a "stupid mistake".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Korsnes |first1=Oscar Strøm |title=Andreas Schjelderup dømt til 14 dagers betinget fengsel – fikk «gult kort» av dommeren
 |url=https://www.nrk.no/sport/andreas-schjelderup-domt-til-14-dagers-betinget-fengsel-_-fikk-_gult-kort_-av-dommeren-1.17658934 |work=NRK |date=19 November 2025 |language=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Short |first1=Michael |title=Norway footballer facing conviction for sharing illegal video |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c986rez00jno |work=BBC |date=9 November 2025}}</ref>

